question: Maya has 5 jars of chocolate chips in her pantry. Each jar of chocolate chips can decorate 6 cupcakes. Maya wants to bake enough cupcakes to use up all of her chocolate chips. If each baking sheet holds 10 cupcakes, how many baking sheets worth of cupcakes should she bake?
answer:
She has enough chocolate chips for 5 * 6 = <<5*6=30>>30 cupcakes.
She needs 30 / 10 = <<30/10=3>>3 baking sheets to bake all of the cupcakes.
